      🚨 Top Breaking Changes Checklist (3.1 → .NET 10)
1. Hosting Model (Biggest Change)
❌ Old (3.1)
Startup.cs + Program.cs
CreateHostBuilder
✅ New
Minimal hosting model (single Program.cs)
What breaks:
Startup configuration won’t wire up the same way
Middleware registration order issues

👉 Action:

Migrate to minimal hosting OR carefully adapt existing Startup pattern
2. Middleware Pipeline Changes
What changed:
Endpoint routing is now mandatory and default
Common issues:
UseRouting() / UseEndpoints() misplacement
Auth middleware order breaks authentication

👉 Action:

Ensure correct order:
app.UseRouting();
app.UseAuthentication();
app.UseAuthorization();
app.MapControllers();
3. Authentication & Identity
Breaking areas:
JWT/Auth configuration APIs updated
Default schemes behave differently
Common issues:
Token validation failures
Middleware not triggering

👉 Action:

Reconfigure authentication using modern patterns (builder.Services.AddAuthentication())
4. JSON Serialization Changes
❌ Old
Newtonsoft.Json (default in many apps)
✅ New
System.Text.Json (default)
Breaking issues:
Case sensitivity differences
Missing features (e.g., custom converters)
Date/time formatting differences

👉 Action:

Either:
Adapt to System.Text.Json
OR explicitly add Newtonsoft back
5. EF Core Changes
Major differences:
Query translation behavior stricter
Client-side evaluation removed
Lazy loading differences
Common breakages:
LINQ queries fail at runtime
Performance regressions

👉 Action:

Rewrite problematic queries
Test all database interactions thoroughly
6. Nullable Reference Types (C#)
Introduced in C# 8, enforced more later
Issues:
Null warnings everywhere
Runtime null bugs exposed

👉 Action:

Enable gradually:
<Nullable>enable</Nullable>
Fix warnings incrementally
7. API Behavior Changes
Examples:
Model validation responses changed
Automatic 400 responses in APIs
Breaking impact:
Existing error handling logic breaks

👉 Action:

Customize behavior:
builder.Services.Configure<ApiBehaviorOptions>(options => { });
8. Configuration Changes
❌ Old
Startup.cs constructor injection
✅ New
builder.Configuration
Issues:
Config not loading correctly
Environment-specific settings break

👉 Action:

Move config usage to new model
9. Logging Changes
Changes:
Logging pipeline improved and simplified
Issues:
Custom logging providers break
Missing logs

👉 Action:

Reconfigure logging in Program.cs
10. Dependency Injection Behavior
Changes:
Stricter validation
Scoped/transient misuse now fails
Issues:
Runtime DI errors
Circular dependencies exposed

👉 Action:

Fix service lifetimes and registrations
11. HTTP Pipeline & Kestrel
Changes:
Stricter defaults
HTTP/2 & HTTP/3 improvements
Issues:
Request size limits
Header validation errors

👉 Action:

Update Kestrel config if needed
12. Razor / MVC Changes
Changes:
Razor compilation updates
Tag helper behavior differences
Issues:
View rendering errors
Build-time failures
13. gRPC / API Protocol Changes

If used:

Config and defaults changed
Serialization differences
14. Removed / Deprecated APIs

Common removals:

Obsolete methods
Legacy hosting APIs
Old cryptography APIs

👉 Action:

Fix compiler errors (they guide you)
15. Package Compatibility Issues (MOST COMMON)
Biggest real-world blocker:
Some NuGet packages:
Not supported beyond 3.1
Abandoned libraries

👉 Action:

Replace with modern alternatives
Upgrade in stages
16. Docker / Hosting Changes
Changes:
New base images
Smaller runtime images
Issues:
Build failures
Runtime mismatches

👉 Action:

Update Dockerfiles:
FROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:10.0
